name: Dar Hamad
description: What is Dar Hamad? Dar Hamad is the epitome of what an authentic Kuwaiti brand should be. The vision of Dar Hamad was to establish a modern brand to immortalize the traditional Kuwaiti culture and allow it to evolve according to the local taste. Modern architecture represents a luxurious atmosphere inspired by Kuwaiti’s unique sense of hospitality. The Design The exterior architecture embodies the rebirth of Al Hamad family house that belonged to the Golden Era of Kuwait’s history. The interior design reflects the traditional Kuwaiti ‘Sandoog’ while incorporating a modern atmosphere. Dar Hamad is comprised of five sections: the Restaurant, Outdoor Terrace, Chai lobby, Banqueting, & Sandoog Boutique. Each section represents a distinctive aspect of the Kuwaiti culture through preparation of only the finest recipes. The Food Experience What makes Dar Hamad complete is its creative implementation of the Kuwaiti cuisine. The cookery was carefully shaped to include influences from The Arabian Peninsula, Persia, India, and the Mediterranean to embrace the entirety of a modern Kuwaiti taste palate. Kuwait’s distinctive hospitality is also represented in the food with rich portion being a central guideline in food presentation. Overall, Dar Hamad is the complete package of Kuwaiti cultural influences, contemporary design and exceptional food craftsmanship. Vision “To become a leading destination in the Gulf Region offering an authentic Kuwaiti cuisine experience and hospitality.” Culture Dar Hamad is an authentic Kuwaiti Brand inspired by memories of the Kuwaiti renaissance era of the 1960’s, 1970’s, and 1980’s. The visual appearance represents a rebirth of the traditional ‘Dar Hamad’ that dates back to the golden era. The base ingredients, which are now the favorites of the local taste buds, allow Dar Hamad’s guests to taste the originality and authenticity of the food experienced back then. Its traditional, unique look and style along with a modern touch sets the ambiance for a high-end, genuinely Kuwaiti experience. name: D'Arcy's Kitchen Shatti
description: After a nice walk on the beach on a breezy day don't forget to pass by D'Arcy's Kitchen. You will be enchanted by our cottage-style interior with its bright & cheerful yellows and blues, folksy decorations and homely gingham seating. The pleasant, and always smiling staff, in their cute country-style outfits, will surround you with warmth and friendliness. As you begin sampling our freshly prepared beverages and wholesome food offerings, you will slowly begin to realize why D'Arcy's holds such a unique place in the hearts & minds of Muscat residents; and why it has twice won the much coveted "Best Cafe Award" since opening its first branch in 1997 in the Shatti Al Qurum beach area. If you're in the mood for a more tranquil experience why not visit our second branch, which is located in a residential area and offers a slightly different and more relaxing experience. With its green & leafy outdoor "English Garden" patios it is reminiscent of pleasant summer living in country villages all over Europe. Over the years D'Arcy's has managed to satisfy its diverse multinational and multicultural customer base by providing a vast selection of items from coffees to juices, from salads to sandwiches, from soups to main dishes, from snacks to desserts. Some of our longtime favorites include our delicious D'Arcy's Breakfast with coffee and juice, refreshing Lime & Mint crushed iced drink, Caesar and Avocado Salads, Traditional Lamb stew, Homemade pies, Tuna and Coronation sandwiches, our famous Steak, Fish & Chips, Aromatic Marinated Chicken, Carrot cake and Sticky Toffee Pudding. Everyone always tells us how at home they feel in D'Arcy's. Whether they're alone, with friends or with the family they always find that spending time at D'Arcy's is both relaxing and rejuvenating. So, give yourself a treat and enjoy a cup of the best cappuccino in town whist reading the latest magazines or having a nice chat with friends.

name: Mais Alghanim
description: The history of Mais Alghanim Restaurant dates back to the previous century when our founding father Edmond Barakat (Abu Emile), opened a canteen for the employees of Yusuf Ahmed Alghanim & Sons Co., called “Mess Alghanim”.Over time, strong ties and personal relations grew between Abu Emile, Kuwaiti, and Expatriate Families extending over three phases and three generations. The first phase commenced in 1953 during which complete meals and take-away services were offered transforming the canteen into a restaurant for one and all.In 1974, Emile Barakat (Abu Edmond) presided over the business from his late father marking the beginning of the second phase. Under his leadership, the restaurant moved to the old Kuwait television station in 1987 where it was registered at the Ministry of Commerce and Industry in the name of Yusuf Ahmed Alghanim & Sons Co. It was at this time that the name was changed from“Mess Alghanim” to “Mais Alghanim”.Abu Edmond’s vision brought Mais Alghanim forward into the beginning of the third phase in 2003, to its present location, a building of true traditional Kuwaiti design, preserving the heritage and genuine tradition. With further development of this phase, Mais Alghanim continued the journey of hospitality by opening its doors to welcome guests at a new location in Mahboula in 2010.Hence, after more than 50 years of successful service, the late Abu Edmond’s brothers and eldest son continue to welcome you with the same spirit through Generations of Genuine Hospitality, and Good Food
